http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kozhikode/PM-to-open-session-at-Ayurveda-fete/article14017590.ece

Prime Minister Narendra Modi will on February 2 inaugurate the Vision Conclave being organised in connection with the third edition of the five-day Global Ayurveda Festival (GAF) in the city.The GAF is being held at Swapna Nagari from January 31 to February 4. It is for the first time Mr. Modi is visiting Kozhikode after he became Prime Minister. The presence of the Prime Minister at the GAF would be a stimulus to the Ayurveda sector, organising committee chief coordinator C. Suresh Kumar and chairman P. Madhavankutty Varier said in a statement here on Saturday.They said that about 5,000 delegates, including 500 foreigners, would take part in the festival. The GAF is considered to be the largest biennial get-together of Ayurveda fraternity. Chief Minister Oommen Chandy will officially inaugurate the GAF on January 31.He will also share the dais with the Prime Minister on February 2.